<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 49ers Sign RB Travis Jervey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Free agent running back Travis Jervey  
signed a contract with the San Francisco 49ers on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Previous reports indicated that the former Green Bay Packer had  
agreed to a four-year deal worth $6 million. The 49ers would not 
release terms of the contract on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Jervey, 26, started five games for the Packers last season  
before breaking his left ankle Nov. 9. He rushed for 325 yards and 
a touchdown before the season-ending injury. 
</P>
<P>
	The fifth-round draft pick out of the Citadel made the Pro-Bowl  
team in 1997 as a special teams player. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
