<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and the Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *MediaOne Group Inc., up 5 7/8 at 66 5/8.  
</P>
<P>
 *Comcast Corp. Class A special common stock, down 7 at 65 7/8 in Nasdaq 
trading. 
</P>
<P>
	Comcast is buying MediaOne for $48.65 billion in stock,  
combining the nation's third- and fourth-largest cable television 
providers. 

</P>
<P>
 *CHS Electronics, down 1 15/16 at 4 1/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The international distributor of microcomputer products, which  
earlier announced it had overstated vendor rebates in the second, 
third and fourth quarters of 1998, said Monday some of the 
fourth-quarter rebates were supported with invalid documentation. A 
senior executive at its European headquarters resigned. 
</P>
<P>
	CHS also announced initiatives designed to reduce operating  
expenses. It reported fourth-quarter income of 23 cents per share, 
down from 45 cents a year ago. 

</P>
<P>
 *U.S. Filter Corp., up 1/16 at 30 9/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	Vivendi, one of France's largest industrial conglomerates, said  
it would buy U.S. Filter in a $6.2 billion, two-step cash deal, 
giving the French company a foothold in the U.S. water-treatment 
business. 

</P>
<P>
 *Jenny Craig Inc., up 15/16 at 4 3/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	Jenny Craig the diet and vitamin company will begin selling a  
line of vitamins, minerals and dietary supplements through its new 
Web site. 

</P>
<P>
 *Gucci Group NV, down 3/8 at 80 5/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	A Dutch Court ruled Monday that Gucci, the Amsterdam-based  
fashion group, must begin negotiations with French luxury-goods 
maker LVMH Moet Hennessey Louis Vuitton over LVMH's $7.86 billion 
offer for Gucci. The court gave LVMH back voting rights on its 26 
percent stake in Gucci, which had been suspended March 3. The court 
also upheld Friday's agreement between French retailer 
Pinault-Printemps-Redoute and Gucci whereby PPR will take a 
40-percent interest in Gucci. However, it suspended any parts of 
the agreement which would hamper the negotiations between Gucci and 
LVMH. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Dell Computer, down 2 1/2 at 37 3/4.    	
</P>
<P>
	Donaldson, Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette Securities trimmed its revenue and  
earnings estimates for the company, saying personal computer sales 
growth will likely be lower in 1999 than in 1998. 

</P>
<P>
 *Broadcast.com, up 29 at 114.  
</P>
<P>
 *Yahoo!, up 2 1/2 at 172 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
	Broadcast.com shares rose on rumors that Yahoo! was about to  
acquire the company. 

</P>
<P>
 *Finet Holdings Corp., up 11/16 at 3 3/4.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company named Gary A. Palmer chief financial officer. Palmer  
has been acting CFO since December. 

</P>
<P>
 *DoubleClick, up 16 5/16 at 196 1/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The Internet advertising company formalized strategic  
partnerships with Comcast Online Communications to develop 
solutions for high-speed online service providers. 


</P>
</TEXT>
