<HEADLINE> 71st Annual Academy Awards Quotes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Quotes from Sunday night's 71st Academy Awards:  
</P>
<P>
	``Winning the Oscar is not the most important thing in the  
world. It's an honor just to be nom... Oh, God. It's my own fault. 
I screwed it up.'' -- ``The Truman Show'' star and Oscar presenter 
Jim Carrey, whose non-nomination was seen by many as a slight. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't feel very deserving of this in your presence.'' -- best  
actress winner Gwyneth Paltrow, sobbing as she named her fellow 
nominees. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm glad it's over, but it was a nice evening.'' -- Elia Kazan  
at a post-Oscar party after receiving a lifetime achievement award 
that created a stir in Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``I've been working and doing this work for, like, over half my  
life and I finally got one right I guess.'' -- James Coburn on 
winning best supporting actor for ``Affliction'' after making more 
than 80 films and never being nominated. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a terrible mistake because I used up all my English.  
... I would like to be Jupiter and kidnap everybody and lie down in 
the firmament making love to everybody.'' -- Roberto Benigni after 
receiving his second Oscar. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Look at this crowd: It's like the million white-man march.'' --  
Presenter Chris Rock as he peered out at the audience. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	'' 'A Bug's Life' -- wasn't that the Linda Tripp story?'' -- Host  
Whoopi Goldberg after the award was given for best animated film. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``And I want to kiss everybody. I would like to thank my parents  
... they gave me the biggest gift of poverty. And I want to thank 
them for that.'' -- Benigni accepting the best foreign film award. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Am I allowed to say I really wanted this? This is fantastic.''  
-- Steven Spielberg accepting best director for ``Saving Private 
Ryan.'' 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``I am the African Queen.'' -- Goldberg, who appeared in full  
regalia and white cake makeup as Queen Elizabeth I. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``We have to follow Academy protocol, Steven Spielberg first,  
the rest of you on your own.'' -- Presenter Robin Williams joking 
about the Academy Award policy on fire evacuations. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Not bad for a goy.'' -- Norman Jewison receiving the Irving G.  
Thalberg Memorial Award, bestowed by the Academy for exemplary 
moviemaking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
