<DOCNO> APW19990322.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-22 19:52:25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gretzky Returns to Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- New York Rangers center Wayne Gretzky's  
return from a neck injury came sooner than expected. 
</P>
<P>
	Gretzky was held scoreless without a shot in 15 shifts --  
totaling 11:15 -- in the Rangers' 6-3 loss to the Tampa Bay 
Lightning Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Gretzky said Sunday's injury to Ulf Samuelsson, who will be  
sidelined two to three weeks with a broken bone in his foot, 
prompted him to inform coach John Muckler on Sunday's flight to 
Tampa that he could play. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was one of those situations where probably if Sammy didn't  
get hurt, I probably would have waited until Wednesday (at 
Florida),'' Gretzky said. ``I felt all right.'' 
</P>
<P>
	After Sunday's game against Pittsburgh, Gretzky said he felt  
fine and hoped to get back into action either against the 
Philadelphia Flyers on Saturday or the New York Islanders on 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gretzky said he wasn't worried about what his role will be in  
Wednesday's contest against the Panthers. 
</P>
<P>
	``I really don't have a big ego as far as what John and the  
coaches want me to do for this team,'' Gretzky said. ``Come 
Wednesday, whatever they want me to do, that's fine with me. All I 
can do is work hard and get ready to go.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Gretzky had been sidelined since Feb. 26.  
</P>
<P>
	The Rangers went 6-3-3 during Gretzky's absence. However, New  
York was 1-3-2 over the final six games without him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
