<HEADLINE> Argentine Boxer Remains in Coma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) - An Argentine boxer remained in  
critical condition Monday after being knocked out in a weekend 
boxing match. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Jorge Guarnieri told reporters Jorge Daniel Alvez is  
breathing with the help of a respirator and suffering from severe 
nuerological complications after he was knocked unconscious 
Saturday night by Dominican boxer, Rosa Gomez. 
</P>
<P>
	Doctors said Monday they were encouraged by a slight improvement  
in Alvez's condition. 
</P>
<P>
	Alvez and Gomez were fighting for the Latin American  
welterweight boxing title in a match sponsored by the World Boxing 
Organization. 
</P>
