<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rapper ODB in Trouble Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Rapper ODB is in trouble again.  
</P>
<P>
	The 30-year-old singer for the Wu-Tang Clan was arrested Monday  
on misdemeanor drug charges after police found he was carrying a 
small amount of crack cocaine, said police spokesman Lt. Dennis 
Cirillo. 
</P>
<P>
	ODB, whose real name is Russell Jones, was stopped by officers  
who allegedly found the drugs when searching his 1996 Range Rover. 
His attorney, Peter Frankell, did not return calls for comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Last month, a Brooklyn grand jury decided Jones would not face  
attempted murder charges after an encounter with officers who 
stopped his car for allegedly not having its lights on. The 
officers said that when they approached the driver's window two 
shots were fired, and they shot back. No gun was found in the car. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones was convicted of second-degree assault in New York in  
1993. 
</P>
<P>
	He was arrested last month in Los Angeles when he parked in a  
no-parking zone and police found he was wearing a bulletproof vest. 
He has pleaded innocent to violating a law banning felons from 
wearing body armor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
