<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brand Wins Oscar Robertson Trophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Elton Brand, the 6-foot-8 sophomore center for  
top-ranked Duke, was named the winner of the Oscar Robertson Trophy 
Monday by the United States Basketball Writers Association. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand was named to both the Associated Press and USBWA first  
team All-America squads and was selected the player of the year in 
the Atlantic Coast Conference. 
</P>
<P>
	He leads Duke in scoring (17.8 points per game) and rebounding  
(9.6 rpg). Brand scored 21 points and pulled down eight rebounds in 
Duke's 85-64 win over Temple Sunday in the East Regional final. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand will be presented the trophy on CBS Sunday during the  
USBWA's college basketball awards show. The Duke star beat out 
Mateen Cleaves of Michigan State, Richard Hamilton of Connecticut, 
Andre Miller of Utah and Jason Terry of Arizona for the honor. 
</P>
<P>
	The Robertson Trophy is the nation's oldest college basketball  
player of the year award. The USBWA has been selecting a player of 
the year since 1959. 
</P>
</TEXT>
