<HEADLINE> Va. Tech Fires Basketball Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BLACKSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Virginia Tech men's basketball coach  
Bobby Hussey was fired Monday after two years with the Hokies. 
</P>
<P>
	Hussey guided Virginia Tech to records of 10-17 and 13-15 after  
replacing Bill Foster as coach before the 1997-98 season. He did 
not attend the news conference and could not be reached for 
comment. 
</P>
<P>
	``It became apparent this season that the program no longer held  
the respect of its fan base,'' said athletic director Jim Weaver. 
``This was evidenced by the poorest attendance in the 38-year 
history of Cassell Coliseum.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The men's team drew an average of 4,040 to the 10,052-seat arena  
this season, more than 1,000 fewer than the women's team. 
</P>
<P>
	Weaver said he made the decision to replace Hussey a few weeks  
ago but waited to announce it because the Hokies women's team was 
in the midst of its deepest run in the NCAA tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	He added that the search for a new coach has begun immediately.  
</P>
