<HEADLINE> Candidate Alexander Targets Gore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Republican presidential candidate Lamar Alexander  
joined the ribbing of Al Gore today by pointing out that the vice 
president, who has claimed credit for the Internet, isn't the only 
inventive Tennesseean. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is true that I, Lamar Alexander, invented plaid,''  
Alexander told the Atlanta Rotary Club, prompting laughter. ``I 
created, myself, the fabric that makes our nation great.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Alexander, a former Tennessee governor who also ran for  
president in 1996, was often seen that year in folksy television 
commercials wearing plaid shirts. 
</P>
<P>
	Gore was widely lampooned by Republicans last week after he  
claimed to have invented the Internet. His comment prompted Senate 
Majority Leader Trent Lott, R-Miss., to claim credit for the paper 
clip. 
</P>
