<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Comcast To Buy MediaOne  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Comcast Corp. is buying MediaOne Group Inc. for  
$48.65 billion in stock, combining the nation's third- and 
fourth-largest cable television providers in the industry's richest 
merger ever. The new Comcast will serve 11 million cable customers 
under the deal announced today, with a potential market of 18 
million homes. Comcast would rank behind only Time Warner Inc. and 
AT&AMP;T Corp., which recently acquired Tele-Communications Inc. 
MediaOne stock jumped 7 3/4 to 68 1/2, but Comcast shares dropped 5 3/8 at 
64 3/4. 

</P>
<P>
	Microsoft To Begin Settlement Talks  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Microsoft Corp. expects to begin negotiations  
with the government soon in an effort to settle its landmark 
antitrust case, but the sides remain far apart on core issues after 
almost five months of an acrimonious courtroom fight. The company 
indicated anew today that it would consider changing some of its 
most controversial agreements with the nation's computer makers and 
Internet providers. But the software giant won't accept 
government-demanded restrictions on what new features it can add to 
its Windows operating system software, which runs roughly 90 
percent of the world's personal computers. 

</P>
<P>
	Stocks Fall, Down Ends Down 13.04  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices fell today, forcing investors to  
contend with the possibility that the Dow Jones industrial average 
might not close above 10,000 any time soon. The blue-chip index 
crossed 10,000 several times last week in intraday trading. Today 
it failed even to do that, meandering throughout the session and 
ending off 13.04 at 9,890.51. That's about 110 points away from 
10,000, but the Dow is still up over 8 percent so far this year. 
Cable TV and Internet stocks provided some upward momentum to the 
technology sector, but personal computer shares sold off, leaving 
the Nasdaq composite down 25.35 at 2,395.92 and the Standard &AMP; 
Poor's 500 index off 2.28 at 1,297.01. 

</P>
