<HEADLINE> Detroit Mercy Fires Women's Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Detroit Mercy women's basketball coach Nikita  
Lowry was fired Monday, the school said. 
</P>
<P>
	Athletic director Brad Kinsman said in a statement that Lowry's  
``philosophical differences with the university'' were behind her 
dismissal and that of her chief assistant Leah Wooldridge. 
</P>
<P>
	Lowry, an assistant at Ohio State before coming to Detroit  
Mercy, had a 48-38 record in three seasons with the Titans. Her 
first team won the Midwestern Collegiate Conference championship 
and reached the NCAA tournament before finishing at 23-7. 
</P>
<P>
	The Titans followed with a 12-16 record in 1997-98 and a 13-15  
mark this past season. 
