<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NCAA Hockey Pairings Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Northern Michigan and Ohio State join Central Collegiate Hockey  
Association regular-season champion Michigan State and tournament 
champion Michigan in the NCAA tournament field announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Northern (22-15-4) finished fifth in the CCHA regular season,  
but beat fourth-place Notre Dame in a best-of-3 series and then 
upset Michigan State in CCHA tournament semifinal before losing 5-1 
in the final to Michigan on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wildcats are seeded fifth in the West Regional and will play  
fourth-seeded Boston College 5:30 p.m. Saturday in Madison, Wis. 
</P>
<P>
	Michigan (24-10-6), which won its fourth CCHA tournament  
championship in six seasons, is a No. 5 seed in the East Regional 
and will play Denver (26-12-2) in Worcester, Mass., 8:30 p.m. 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Denver won the WCHA Final Five tournament in Minneapolis  
Saturday night with a 4-3 upset of North Dakota. 
</P>
<P>
	The Spartans, who have lost only twice in their last 27 games,  
is a No. 2 seed in Madison. They will play 3 p.m. Sunday against 
the winner of Saturday's game between St. Lawrence (23-12-3) and 
Colorado College (28-11-1). 
</P>
<P>
	The sixth-seeded Buckeyes (21-15-4) face Maine (27-6-4) 5 p.m.  
Friday in Worcester. 
</P>
<P>
	WCHA regular-season champion North Dakota got a bye for the  
first round of this coming weekend's NCAA Division I hockey 
tournament when pairings were announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Next Sunday, North Dakota will play the winner of Saturday's  
game between Boston College and Northern Michigan in the West 
Regional at Madison, Wis. 
</P>
<P>
	The winners of the regional contests advance to the Frozen Four  
in Anaheim, Calif., April 1 and April 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
